cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it deals with mobile ad-hoc networks and wireless mesh networks. It could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as it deals with routing protocols. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it discusses the use of sequence numbers in routing protocols. It could also be classified under cs.IT (Information Theory) as it discusses the assumptions made in resolving ambiguities in the RFC. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the use of AODV-based protocols.
